author: Scott Donaldson
title: New Zealand men's sprint team wins at Oceania Track Cycling Championships
text:
New Zealand men's sprint team wins at Oceania Track Cycling Championships SCOTT DONALDSON Last updated 19:58, October 8 2015 GETTY IMAGES 
Ethan Mitchell, left, Sam Webster and Eddie Dawkins show their power in qualifying for the men's team sprint at the Oceania Track Cycling Championships in Invercargill. 
The New Zealand team have won the elite men's team sprint team beating Australia on the opening night of the 2016 Oceania Track Cycling Championships in Invercargill. 
The 2014 world championship-winning Kiwi combination featuring Southland rider Eddie Dawkins, Sam Webster and Ethan Mitchell won the race in a time of 43.810 seconds, beating the Australian combination of Patrick Constable, Matthew Glaetzer and Jacob Schmid who finished with a time of 44.376sec. 
Australian riders Anna Meares and Kaarle McCulloch won the women's team sprint.
